    "collage_cpYDQ9": {
      "type": "collage",
      "blocks": {
        "text_bntL6K": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Cut",
            "heading_size": "h4",
            "heading_size_mobile": "h4-mobile",
            "text": "Often considered the most important 'C', the cut determines how well a diamond interacts with light. A masterfully cut diamond will capture light and return it as a breathtaking display of brilliance, fire, and scintillation. It's the only 'C' influenced directly by human artistry.",
            "url": "shopify://blogs/guide-bespoke-engagement-ring-design/cut-the-4cs-of-a-diamond",
            "button_label": "Learn More",
            "buttons_style": "underlined",
            "override_button_colors": false,
            "button_background_color": "#e68819",
            "button_color": "#ffffff",
            "desktop_position": "md-min-align-top md-min-justify-left",
            "text_alignment": "left",
            "background_color": "rgba(0,0,0,0)",
            "text_color": "#242424"
          }
        },
        "text_F7wdVc": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Clarity",
            "heading_size": "h4",
            "heading_size_mobile": "h4-mobile",
            "text": "Clarity measures the presence of internal characteristics (inclusions) and external characteristics (blemishes). Diamonds with fewer and smaller inclusions receive higher clarity grades.",
            "url": "shopify://blogs/guide-bespoke-engagement-ring-design/clarity-the-4cs-of-a-diamond",
            "button_label": "Learn More",
            "buttons_style": "underlined",
            "override_button_colors": false,
            "button_background_color": "#e68819",
            "button_color": "#ffffff",
            "desktop_position": "md-min-align-top md-min-justify-left",
            "text_alignment": "left",
            "background_color": "rgba(0,0,0,0)",
            "text_color": "#242424"
          }
        },
        "text_UiG8mi": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Carat",
            "heading_size": "h4",
            "heading_size_mobile": "h4-mobile",
            "text": "The carat is the unit of measurement for a diamond's weight. While larger diamonds are rarer and more valuable, the other 3Cs also significantly impact a diamond's overall quality.",
            "url": "shopify://blogs/guide-bespoke-engagement-ring-design/carat-the-4cs-of-a-diamond",
            "button_label": "Learn More",
            "buttons_style": "underlined",
            "override_button_colors": false,
            "button_background_color": "#e68819",
            "button_color": "#ffffff",
            "desktop_position": "md-min-align-top md-min-justify-left",
            "text_alignment": "left",
            "background_color": "rgba(0,0,0,0)",
            "text_color": "#242424"
          }
        },
        "text_hmVTby": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Colour",
            "heading_size": "h4",
            "heading_size_mobile": "h4-mobile",
            "text": "Diamond colour is graded on a scale from D (colourless) to Z (light yellow or brown). The most valuable diamonds are those that are colourless, as they allow the most light to pass through, creating maximum brilliance.",
            "url": "shopify://blogs/guide-bespoke-engagement-ring-design/colour-the-4cs-of-a-diamond",
            "button_label": "Learn More",
            "buttons_style": "underlined",
            "override_button_colors": false,
            "button_background_color": "#e68819",
            "button_color": "#ffffff",
            "desktop_position": "md-min-align-top md-min-justify-left",
            "text_alignment": "left",
            "background_color": "rgba(0,0,0,0)",
            "text_color": "#242424"
          }
        },
        "text_3QhWD6": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "The Modern Choice: Lab Diamonds",
            "heading_size": "h4",
            "heading_size_mobile": "h4-mobile",
            "text": "Embrace the future of fine jewellery. Lab-grown diamonds offer a conscious, beautiful, and identical alternative to their natural counterparts. They are chemically, physically, and optically the same as mined diamonds.",
            "url": "shopify://blogs/guide-lab-diamonds/why-lab-grown-diamonds-are-the-ethical-future-of-jewellery",
            "button_label": "Learn About Lab Diamonds",
            "buttons_style": "underlined",
            "override_button_colors": false,
            "button_background_color": "#e68819",
            "button_color": "#ffffff",
            "desktop_position": "md-min-align-top md-min-justify-left",
            "text_alignment": "center",
            "background_color": "#f8f7f2",
            "text_color": "#242424"
          }
        }
      },
